# Why Feature Engineering?

Raw predictor columns are rarely in the best form for a model. **Feature
engineering** reshapes and enriches predictors so a model can extract
signal more efficiently.

Common motivations:

| Motivation | Example |
|---------------------------------------------|---------------------------|
| Represent non-linear patterns | spline expansion of latitude |
| Put predictors on a common scale | `step_normalize()` |
| Reduce correlated predictors | PCA via `step_pca()` |
| Encode qualitative data numerically | `step_dummy()` |
| Handle rare categories | `step_other()` |
| Impute missing values | `step_impute_mean()` |

::: callout-tip
## Marketing relevance

In marketing datasets you'll routinely encounter: sparse categorical
variables (campaign IDs, product SKUs), skewed spend/revenue columns,
and high-dimensional customer segments. `recipes` handles all of these
in a reproducible, pipeline-safe way.
:::

