# Skipping Steps for New Data (`skip = TRUE`)

Some steps should only run during training — never on new/test data.

```{r skip-demo}
#| eval: false
# WRONG — will fail at predict time because Sale_Price won't exist
bad_recipe <-
  recipe(Sale_Price ~ ., data = ames_train) %>%
  step_log(Sale_Price, base = 10) # outcome transformation inside recipe

# RIGHT — transform the outcome BEFORE building the recipe
ames <- ames %>% mutate(Sale_Price = log10(Sale_Price))
```

Steps that automatically set `skip = TRUE`:

-   `step_downsample()`, `step_upsample()`, `step_smote()`
-   `step_filter()`, `step_sample()`, `step_slice()`, `step_naomit()`

You can set `skip = TRUE` manually on any step when needed.

