# Column Roles

Beyond `"predictor"` and `"outcome"`, you can assign **custom roles** to
columns so they ride along during resampling without being used as model
inputs.

```{r column-roles-demo}
#| eval: false
# Suppose ames had an 'address' column we want to keep for audit purposes:
ames_rec_with_id <-
  ames_rec %>%
  update_role(address, new_role = "street address")

# A column can have multiple roles:
ames_rec %>%
  add_role(Neighborhood, new_role = "grouping variable")
```

This is especially valuable when **resampling** (Chapter 10) — keeping
auxiliary columns in the same data frame avoids error-prone external
vector joins.

