## Exercise 4 — Marketing Dataset Application

> **Context:** You are working on a customer churn prediction model for a
> telecommunications company. The dataset contains:
>
> -   `Churn` — binary outcome (Yes/No)
> -   `MonthlyCharges` — continuous, right-skewed
> -   `TotalCharges` — continuous, right-skewed, has some `NA` values
> -   `Contract` — factor (Month-to-month, One year, Two year)
> -   `InternetService` — factor (DSL, Fiber optic, No)
> -   `tenure` — numeric (months with company)
> -   `CustomerID` — identifier column (should not be a predictor)

Build a recipe that:

a.  Assigns `CustomerID` the role `"id"` using `update_role()` so it
    rides along without being used in the model.
b.  Applies `step_log(MonthlyCharges, TotalCharges, base = 10)` for
    skew correction.
c.  Imputes missing `TotalCharges` with the median via
    `step_impute_median()`.
d.  Creates an interaction between `MonthlyCharges` and each
    `Contract` dummy.
e.  Pools any `InternetService` level with fewer than 5% of rows into
    "other".
f.  Prints the recipe and explains in a comment what each step does and
    why it is placed in that order.

```{r ex4-solution}
#| code-fold: true
#| code-summary: "Show solution"
#| eval: false
#| echo: false
# Simulate a small telco dataset for illustration
set.seed(42)
n <- 500
telco_train <- tibble(
  CustomerID = paste0("C", seq_len(n)),
  Churn = factor(sample(
    c("Yes", "No"),
    n,
    replace = TRUE,
    prob = c(0.27, 0.73)
  )),
  MonthlyCharges = rgamma(n, shape = 3, rate = 0.04),
  TotalCharges = ifelse(runif(n) < 0.03, NA, rgamma(n, shape = 5, rate = 0.01)),
  Contract = factor(sample(
    c("Month-to-month", "One year", "Two year"),
    n,
    replace = TRUE,
    prob = c(0.55, 0.25, 0.20)
  )),
  InternetService = factor(sample(
    c("DSL", "Fiber optic", "No"),
    n,
    replace = TRUE,
    prob = c(0.34, 0.44, 0.22)
  )),
  tenure = rpois(n, lambda = 32)
)

telco_recipe <-
  recipe(
    Churn ~ MonthlyCharges +
      TotalCharges +
      Contract +
      InternetService +
      tenure +
      CustomerID,
    data = telco_train
  ) %>%
  # Step 0: remove CustomerID from modelling (keep it as an ID column)
  update_role(CustomerID, new_role = "id") %>%
  # Step 1: impute before transforming — log(0) or log(NA) would fail
  step_impute_median(TotalCharges) %>%
  # Step 2: log-transform right-skewed continuous predictors
  step_log(MonthlyCharges, TotalCharges, base = 10) %>%
  # Step 3: pool rare InternetService levels (if any fall below 5%)
  step_other(InternetService, threshold = 0.05) %>%
  # Step 4: create dummy variables (must precede step_interact)
  step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors()) %>%
  # Step 5: interaction — monthly charges × contract type dummies
  step_interact(~ MonthlyCharges:starts_with("Contract_"))

telco_recipe
```

