# Chapter 8 — Key Takeaways

| Concept | What to remember |
|-------------------------------|--------------------------------------|
| `recipe()` | Specifies steps; estimation deferred to `fit()` |
| `step_other()` | Pool rare factor levels **before** `step_dummy()` |
| `step_dummy()` | Converts factors to binary columns; use `one_hot = TRUE` if needed |
| `step_interact()` | Must run **after** `step_dummy()` |
| `step_ns()` | Spline expansion; `deg_free` is a tuning parameter |
| `step_pca()` | Compress correlated columns; normalize first |
| `step_mutate()` | Flexible hand-crafted features; watch for leakage |
| `skip = TRUE` | Subsampling steps only affect training data |
| `tidy()` | Inspect what the recipe learned from training data |
| `update_role()` | Keep ID/audit columns without using them as predictors |

